<div style="text-align: center; padding: 20px; background-color: #f7f7f7; border-radius: 12px; font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;">
<h1 style="color: #0d9488; font-size: 2.5rem; font-weight: 700;">Considering Your Skin Cancer Treatment Options?</h1>
<p style="color: #4b5563; font-size: 1.25rem; margin-top: 10px;">A non-surgical alternative for basal cell and squamous cell carcinomas</p>
</div>

<div style="padding: 30px;">
<div style="background-color: #ffffff; border-radius: 12px; box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1); padding: 25px; margin-bottom: 20px;">
<h2 style="color: #0d9488; font-size: 1.75rem; border-bottom: 2px solid #e5e7eb; padding-bottom: 10px;">What is Superficial Radiation Therapy (SRT)?</h2>
<p style="color: #374151; margin-top: 15px; line-height: 1.6;">
Superficial Radiation Therapy (SRT) is a highly effective, non-invasive treatment option for non-melanoma skin cancers. It uses a targeted, low-energy X-ray beam to destroy cancer cells on the skin's surface without the need for cutting or stitches. The radiation only penetrates about 5mm deep, which helps protect healthy underlying tissue.
</p>
</div>

<div style="display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 20px; justify-content: center;">
<div style="flex: 1 1 300px; background-color: #ffffff; border-radius: 12px; box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1); padding: 25px;">
<h3 style="color: #0d9488; font-size: 1.5rem; border-bottom: 2px solid #e5e7eb; padding-bottom: 10px;">Key Benefits</h3>
<ul style="color: #374151; list-style-type: none; padding: 0; margin-top: 15px;">
<li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">&#10003; <strong>Non-Surgical:</strong> No cutting, no stitches, and no surgical scarring.</li>
<li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">&#10003; <strong>Minimal Downtime:</strong> Return to your daily activities immediately after treatment.</li>
<li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">&#10003; <strong>Painless:</strong> The procedure is quick and virtually painless, with no anesthesia required.</li>
<li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">&#10003; <strong>High Success Rate:</strong> Proven to be a highly effective treatment for appropriate skin cancers.</li>
</ul>
</div>

<div style="flex: 1 1 300px; background-color: #ffffff; border-radius: 12px; box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1); padding: 25px;">
  <h3 style="color: #0d9488; font-size: 1.5rem; border-bottom: 2px solid #e5e7eb; padding-bottom: 10px;">What to Expect</h3>
  <ul style="color: #374151; list-style-type: none; padding: 0; margin-top: 15px;">
    <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">&#9888; <strong>Treatment Sessions:</strong> Typically administered over several sessions, depending on your diagnosis.</li>
    <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">&#9888; <strong>In-Office Procedure:</strong> Your treatment will be performed in a comfortable outpatient setting.</li>
    <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">&#9888; <strong>Localized Side Effects:</strong> Possible side effects may include temporary redness or irritation in the treated area.</li>
  </ul>
</div>

</div>

<div style="background-color: #e0f2f1; border-radius: 12px; padding: 25px; text-align: center; margin-top: 20px;">
<h3 style="color: #0d9488; font-size: 1.5rem;">Is SRT the Right Choice for You?</h3>
<p style="color: #374151; margin-top: 10px;">
SRT is a great option for many patients, especially those who prefer to avoid surgery, have lesions on cosmetically sensitive areas, or are not candidates for surgery due to other health conditions.
</p>
<p style="color: #374151; margin-top: 10px;">
To learn more and find out if SRT is the right treatment for your skin cancer, schedule a consultation with a qualified dermatologist.
</p>
</div>
</div>
